description:
Zestimate® Home Value: $367,123. "18 foot ceilings" 

This spacious 3/3/ two-story walkout is loaded with builder upgrades, which sets this house a few notches above the rest of the development. Basic structure is bigger: We added the builder upgrade of $15K (in 2003 dollars) to add 3 feet on three perimeter walls from basement to second floor. This significantly increased the size of all major rooms and bedroom.  The spacious family room already has surround sound with 18 ft. high ceilings up to the loft.  The loft can be used as a nice office den or play area. The builder had an option to create  4th bedroom there, so it most likely is convert-able.

With nearly 1,000 SF of unfinished basement, the walkout basement has builder upgraded outdoor cement patio base, windowed to add 4th bedroom and builder plumbed to add a full bath.  A hobbyist may leave it for a large shop or the growing family may add the 4th bedroom and recreation area. There is enough space for a home theater, pool table or up to your imagination. 

Rain gutters installed.

Most homes in Savanna have downstairs laundry. We paid builder for upgraded main floor laundry! Who wants to climb 2 flights of stairs with full laundry baskets? Here, it is just a few steps upstairs to the bedrooms with your laundry. 
The best part: Enjoy the clean, crisp Woodbury outdoors in the 16 x 9 SCREENED-in 3-season deck. It proposes serenity as it overlooks Marsh Creek woods. Whether you are enjoying an early cup of java and listening to the birds or watching deer play in the woods, you will love the little sanctuary of nearly 150 SF of screened-in deck. It also makes a great Zen place for morning Yoga as the sun rises on the east facing deck. This also makes great evenings with friends over for a cool evening dinner. The deck area is wired for speakers, which lead to the home entertainment system area. If you want a 4-season, the deck footings are code to support a 4-season upgrade - another equity building option because you will add valuable livable square footage at a small cost - Add a TV and gas fireplace while enjoying a warm view of the winter snowfalls. It gets better: Connected to the screened deck is an equally sized OPEN-Air deck. This equals nearly 300 SF of deck overlooking the woods and stairs to the back yard. Bonus: the open deck has access from the dining room with full-size sliding glass door (builder upgrade). Other homes in Savanna Oaks only have a small window in that place. Under the open deck is the pad for the walkout basement. A future patio or hot tub would nicely fit there. Security system with pet-friendly motion detection. 

The NEW roof ($10K) is complete, NEW Genz-Ryan installed Lennox Air Conditioning ($2K) unit is installed and a $650 NEW stainless dishwasher is installed.  New Vinyl Plank kitchen and bathrooms floor! (08/11/16). Driveway re-sealed! A few notes: Gas furnace newer motor and newer gas water heater. Newer stainless appliances. HE washer and gas dryer. Water softener.  Hunter underground sprinkler. More photos coming.  And yes, that is a cherry tree at the front corner of the house. Welcome home!

Recently sold: $289,900. Welcome to 9300 Hillingdon Road! This lovely home will impress you the moment you step through the front door with its vaulted ceilings, sunlit filled rooms, gleaming hardwood floors, and spacious backyard.

The informal dining room welcomes you in and will be an ideal place to host family and friends for holiday celebrations and intimate gatherings alike. Floor to ceiling windows look out to the deck and allow light to fill this room all year long. The open layout between this space and kitchen means socializing with your guests is fun and easy.

The home?s kitchen boasts beautiful silestone counters, shaker cabinets, and stone-tiled backsplashes. Pull up to the breakfast bar for weekend pancakes!  Whipping up your favorite recipes here is a breeze thanks to ample counter space and abundant cabinetry to house your cookware.

Travel to the upper level to find the living room which features soft, neutral carpeting, wonderful views across the backyard, and a vaulted ceiling. What a great place for movie nights or to relax with your newest book as you soak up the natural daylight.

Two bedrooms sit on this level as well, one of which is the owner?s suite with a walk-in closet and a walk-through bathroom ensuite featuring craftsman tile.


A lower level lays claim to a brick-faced, gas fireplace; what an ideal spot to sit on a cool morning with a cup of coffee in front of the fire. This room is spacious and flooded with daylight thanks to windows lining the wall offering views out to the backyard. Along the hallway you will find the third bedroom, a ¾ bathroom, and great storage. 

An attached two car garage will keep your cars and toys free from the elements year round. Soak up the warm sunshine on the deck or host barbecues with friends on long Fall days! A fully fenced backyard will allow your four-legged friends to explore worry free. Let your green thumb shape the yard thanks to ample sunlight. Store tools with ease in the shed!

Stepping out your front door, miles of walking, biking, and running trails can be found just minutes away around Colby Lake. A short drive will bring you to numerous shops and some of Woodbury?s most delicious restaurants! A quick commute along nearby I94 places you in downtown St. Paul or Hudson in under twenty minutes. Don?t miss your chance to call this home.

Please contact Team Edelstein at 651-695-4300 or Team@TeamEdelstein.com with any questions or to learn more! We would be happy to speak with you!

description: Recently sold: $717,000. Starting in the two-story great room, you'll love the loads of natural daylight that pour in from its wall of windows, along with its stunning, floor-to-ceiling fireplace and private views of your treed backyard.  And in the spacious kitchen, you'll appreciate an abundance of white enamel cabinetry and Corian counter space, along with high-end appliances, a wine fridge, walk-in pantry and large center island with granite countertop.  In addition, a cozy sunroom with a built-in window seat is the perfect retreat to enjoy your morning coffee and views of the outdoor pool in the fenced-in backyard, and an informal dining space, as well as seating at the island provide extra dining options, in addition to the elegant formal dining room.  To finish off the main level is a functional office with built-in workstations, desirable laundry room and mudroom with built-ins.  On the upper level, you'll find another built-in dual workstation in the open loft and three spacious bedrooms with walk-in closets and accommodating en suite baths, including the expansive master suite that features a vaulted tray ceiling, electric fireplace and oversized en suite with a two-person walk-in shower, whirlpool tub and huge dressing room. description: Recently sold: $368,900. This home is a Real Estate Owned (REO)/Post Foreclosure. Once a lender has foreclosed on a property it is soon put up for public auction. If bids fall short of the asking price the bank will buy back the home and attempt to sell it on the open market. However, lenders are not real estate agents, meaning that they will often accept offers 30 to 60 percent less than market value!

description: Recently sold: $559,000. With tremendous potential and all the space you could ask for, put your personal touches on a home you would be proud to call your own.

Recently sold: $485,000. Updates galore, wooded walkout w/sport court. Enormous kitchen, media center, billiard area, wine cellar. Every room will impress. Access to trails, parks and Lake Wilmes.

Neighborhood Description
